{"word":"φυτουργός","slug":"φυτουργός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φυτουργός</b></el> <el>(φῠτ-ουργός, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>Ἔργω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>working at plants;</i> as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a gardener, vinedresser</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>begetting</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: <i>the author</i> of a thing, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}